The structure-from-motion (SFM) problem is a fundamental computer vision task which aims to recover camera parameters such as position, rotation and translation for 3D points observed on static scenes or moving cameras. This can be used to generate accurate reconstructions of objects' shapes or their motions over time.

The main challenge lies in estimating the large number of degrees of freedom (DOFs). There are several factors that make it particularly challenging:
* Many points need to be tracked at high frame rates; 
* The geometry may not have a well defined center of mass, resulting in singularities in the Jacobian; 
